---
title: "Formation of Multiple Black Holes from Cauchy Data (joint with Dawei Shen)"
collection: publications
date: 2025-06-19
venue: ""
excerpt: "We construct vacuum initial data whose evolution leads to the formation of multiple causally independent trapped surfaces."
paperurl: "https://arxiv.org/abs/2506.16117"
area: gr
status: preprint
---

In this paper, we construct asymptotically flat Cauchy initial data for the Einstein vacuum equations containing no trapped surfaces, whose future development leads to the formation of multiple causally independent trapped surfaces and hence multiple black holes in finite time.
